---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-32 lg:pt-30 lg:pb-40">
    <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl xl:text-8xl font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-tighter max-w-[700px] mb-12">
      The interface<br/>
      <span class="text-fg-tertiary">is changing.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-[17px] leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary max-w-[520px] mb-8">
      Bird Candy is a strategy studio helping companies navigate the shift from
      proprietary platforms to open protocols. We work with AT Protocol — the
      standard behind Bluesky — to help organizations that are rethinking how
      they publish, distribute, and own their data.
    </p>
    <a href="#contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-fg no-underline border-b border-rule pb-0.5 transition-[border-color] duration-150 hover:border-accent">
      Get in touch &rarr;
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- THE SHIFT -->
  <section class="py-20 fade-in" id="the-shift">
    <hr class="border-t border-rule mb-12" />
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-fg-tertiary mb-12">The shift</p>

    <p class="text-2xl lg:text-4xl font-medium leading-snug tracking-tight max-w-[640px] mb-16">
      For two decades, the most valuable companies on the internet have been
      databases with interfaces. The app was how you reached the data. The data
      was the moat.
    </p>

    <div class="max-w-[600px] space-y-5">
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        That model is breaking — from multiple directions at once.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        AI agents are becoming the primary interface. When a user asks an agent
        to act on their behalf, the agent doesn't open your app — it needs
        structured, open data it can read and transact with. If your data isn't
        accessible, you're invisible.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        Regulators are demanding portability. Users are expecting ownership. And
        open protocols are making it possible to publish data in formats that
        anyone — any app, any agent, any competitor — can build on.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        The companies that adapt will define the standards their industries run
        on. The ones that don't will find themselves intermediated by someone who
        did.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- AT Protocol -->
    <p class="text-2xl lg:text-4xl font-medium leading-snug tracking-tight max-w-[640px] mt-16 mb-12">
      AT Protocol is the most credible infrastructure for this transition.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="border-t border-rule pt-8 pb-8 pr-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-accent-blue mb-4">01</p>
        <h3 class="text-[17px] font-medium tracking-tight mb-2">Identity</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Verifiable identity tied to your domain. Portable, cryptographic,
          owned by you — not rented from a platform.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t md:border-l border-rule pt-8 pb-8 pr-8 md:pl-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-accent-blue mb-4">02</p>
        <h3 class="text-[17px] font-medium tracking-tight mb-2">Content</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Data stored on infrastructure you control. Syndicates across every app
          in the network. Switch platforms, keep your audience.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t md:border-l border-rule pt-8 pb-8 md:pl-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-accent-blue mb-4">03</p>
        <h3 class="text-[17px] font-medium tracking-tight mb-2">Interoperability</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Open schemas — Lexicons — that make your data machine-readable by
          default. Agents, apps, and competitors can all build on it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Momentum stats -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 border-t border-b border-rule mt-12">
      <div class="py-8 pr-6">
        <div class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight mb-1">43M+</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-fg-tertiary leading-snug">Bluesky users</div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-rule py-8 px-6">
        <div class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight mb-1">$100M</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-fg-tertiary leading-snug">Series B, 2026</div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-rule py-8 px-6">
        <div class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight mb-1">IETF</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-fg-tertiary leading-snug">Standardization underway</div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l border-rule py-8 pl-6">
        <div class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight mb-1">1,000+</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-fg-tertiary leading-snug">Weekly active apps</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
  <section class="py-20 fade-in" id="capabilities">
    <hr class="border-t border-rule mb-12" />
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-fg-tertiary mb-12">What we do</p>

    <!-- Strategy -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[180px_1fr] gap-8 md:gap-16 py-10 border-t border-rule items-baseline">
      <div class="text-sm font-medium tracking-tight">Strategy</div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_200px] gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Where does AT Protocol fit in your business? We map the opportunity,
          identify what to build first, and produce a roadmap your team can
          execute against.
        </p>
        <div class="text-[13px] leading-loose text-fg-tertiary">
          <span class="block">Readiness assessment</span>
          <span class="block">Opportunity mapping</span>
          <span class="block">Executive roadmap</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[180px_1fr] gap-8 md:gap-16 py-10 border-t border-rule items-baseline">
      <div class="text-sm font-medium tracking-tight">Architecture</div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_200px] gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Identity systems, Lexicon design, data models, feed algorithms. The
          technical foundations that make your protocol presence buildable,
          maintainable, and interoperable.
        </p>
        <div class="text-[13px] leading-loose text-fg-tertiary">
          <span class="block">System design</span>
          <span class="block">Identity strategy</span>
          <span class="block">Lexicon design</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Prototyping -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[180px_1fr] gap-8 md:gap-16 py-10 border-t border-b border-rule items-baseline">
      <div class="text-sm font-medium tracking-tight">Prototyping</div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_200px] gap-8 lg:gap-12">
        <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
          Small, fast implementations built outside your production environment.
          Test the thesis before you commit the roadmap.
        </p>
        <div class="text-[13px] leading-loose text-fg-tertiary">
          <span class="block">Custom feeds</span>
          <span class="block">Integration prototypes</span>
          <span class="block">Technical validation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY A STUDIO -->
  <section class="py-20 fade-in" id="why-studio">
    <hr class="border-t border-rule mb-12" />
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-fg-tertiary mb-12">Why a studio</p>

    <div class="max-w-[600px] space-y-5">
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        This transition requires a different kind of thinking than your team is
        staffed for. Not because they aren't capable — because the mental model
        is different. Centralized architecture and decentralized protocols are
        fundamentally different design problems.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        We provide protocol fluency. We've internalized how identity, data, and
        distribution work in a federated system so your team doesn't have to
        start from zero.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-fg-secondary">
        And when the work involves defining open standards, neutrality matters. A
        schema designed by one platform will be resisted by its competitors. We
        sit outside that dynamic — which is exactly where this work needs to
        happen.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTACT -->
  <section class="pt-30 pb-20 fade-in" id="contact">
    <hr class="border-t border-rule mb-12" />
    <p class="text-2xl lg:text-4xl font-medium leading-snug tracking-tight max-w-[500px] mb-6">
      Let's talk about what you're thinking.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-fg-secondary mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-[440px]">
      No contact form, no email funnel. We take conversations the way the open
      network is meant to work — a direct, end-to-end encrypted message over AT
      Protocol.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
      <a
        href="https://bsky.app/profile/birdcandy.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="group inline-flex items-center justify-between gap-6 border border-rule px-5 py-4 no-underline transition-colors duration-150 hover:border-fg"
      >
        <span>
          <span class="block text-sm font-medium tracking-tight">Message us on Bluesky</span>
          <span class="block font-mono text-[13px] text-fg-tertiary">@birdcandy.com</span>
        </span>
        <span class="text-fg-tertiary transition-colors duration-150 group-hover:text-fg">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-fg-tertiary max-w-[440px]">
      DMs are end-to-end encrypted via
      <a href="https://www.germnetwork.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="border-b border-rule pb-px transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-accent hover:border-accent">Germ</a>
      — no separate account needed, just your Bluesky handle.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <footer class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-start sm:items-center gap-4 border-t border-rule py-8 text-xs text-fg-tertiary">
    <span>Bird Candy &copy; 2026</span>
    <ul class="flex gap-5 list-none p-0">
      <li><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/birdcandy.com" class="text-fg-tertiary no-underline transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-accent" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bluesky</a></li>
    </ul>
  </footer>

</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('visible');
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });

  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>

<style>
  .fade-in {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(16px);
    transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease;
  }
  .fade-in.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
</style>
